text: Ypsolopha nigrimaculata is a moth of the family Ypsolophidae. It is known from Korea and the Russian Far East.New taxonomic data on the genus Ypsolopha Latreille (Lepidoptera, Ypsolophidae) with descriptions of two new species from the Russian Far East The length of the forewings is about 11 mm.LepTree ==References== Category:Moths described in 2001 Category:Ypsolophidae Category:Moths of Asia
title: Ypsolopha nigrimaculata
